         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>53</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... because of the greed of the living beings the poverty of a single birth indeed, the big, old [ones] ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>404</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>53</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... they realize/fulfil the wish for one single birth indeed, because of the sufferings in innumerable Kalpas ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>257</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1988"/><citedRange>253</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the merit arises through giving alms. A meritorious king has founded this [gift] for a cloister, therefore (the state) of the cloister ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>34</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... or when there was a king named Kaniṣka, ... in the Law ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/><citedRange>97</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>111</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (Kaniṣka rebuilt?) cloister [and] monasteries having been destroyed by the king Puṣyamitra ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (it has been) said by the Law abiding king [= Dharmarāja] ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [the] cloister; therefore he is called Dharmarāja. ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [the stūpa is] wide [and] straight. In height a hundred miles far from the earth ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>144</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>129f</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>113, 406</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>107</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [the stūpa] differs [= is superior] in height like the (Sumeru) mountain. It contains relics in its shrine. Therefore it [belongs to] a Dha(rmarāja). ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Im Inneren trägt er die Reliquien.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Inside he bears the relics.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>406</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... wie der ... -Berg unterscheidet er sich durch die Höhe.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... like the ... -mountain it differs in height.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>113</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the cloister founded by the Law abiding king Śpeśu from all cloisters ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... thus indeed ... the cloister founded by the Law abiding king Kaniṣka (from) all (cloisters) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>105</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... they (say): "Whenever there are (bi)g cloisters provided with relics, all these [belong to] Dharma(rāja) [kings] ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
